"<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en"><head><meta charSet="utf-8"/><meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1"/><title>Jane Doe — I build accessible, pixel-perfect experiences for the web.</title><meta name="description" content="Jane builds accessible, pixel-perfect interfaces for large-scale products."/><meta name="author" content="Jane Doe"/><link rel="canonical" href="https://jane.example.test"/><meta property="og:title" content="Jane Doe — I build accessible, pixel-perfect experiences for the web."/><meta property="og:description" content="Jane builds accessible, pixel-perfect interfaces for large-scale products."/><meta property="og:type" content="website"/><meta property="og:url" content="https://jane.example.test"/><meta property="og:image" content="/og.png"/><meta property="og:image:width" content="1200"/><meta property="og:image:height" content="630"/><meta property="og:image:alt" content="Jane Doe — portfolio"/><meta name="twitter:card" content="summary_large_image"/><meta name="twitter:title" content="Jane Doe — I build accessible, pixel-perfect experiences for the web."/><meta name="twitter:description" content="Jane builds accessible, pixel-perfect interfaces for large-scale products."/><meta name="twitter:image" content="/og.png"/><link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.googleapis.com"/><link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.gstatic.com" crossorigin="anonymous"/><link href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Fraunces:ital,opsz,wght@0,9..144,400;0,9..144,500;0,9..144,600;1,9..144,500&amp;family=Inter:wght@400;500;600&amp;family=JetBrains+Mono:wght@400;500&amp;display=swap" rel="stylesheet"/><style>/* fixture */</style></head><body><header class="topbar"><div class="container topbar-inner"><div class="brand"><a href="/">Jane Doe</a></div><nav aria-label="Primary"><ul class="nav-links"><li><a href="/">Home</a></li><li><a href="/projects/" class="active">Work</a></li><li><a href="/about/">About</a></li><li><a href="/contact/">Contact</a></li></ul></nav><span class="status-chip">Available for new work</span></div></header><main><article class="section"><div class="container"><div class="section-header"><h2>Signal Forge</h2><p>Open-source project · 4.2k stars · 23 contributors</p></div><ul class="pwb-credibility-byline" aria-label="Project credibility signals"><li class="pwb-credibility-chip"><span class="pwb-credibility-category">OSS Author</span></li><li class="pwb-credibility-chip"><span>23 contributors</span></li><li class="pwb-credibility-chip"><span title="This repo runs continuous integration on every push"><span aria-hidden="true">✓</span> CI</span></li><li class="pwb-credibility-chip"><span title="This repo declares a test framework"><span aria-hidden="true">✓</span> Tests</span></li><li class="pwb-credibility-chip"><span title="This repo publishes versioned releases"><span aria-hidden="true">✓</span> Releases</span></li><li class="pwb-credibility-chip"><a class="pwb-credibility-live" href="https://signal-forge.example.test" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Live <span aria-hidden="true">→</span></a></li></ul><ul class="outcome-row" style="margin-bottom:32px"><li class="outcome-chip"><b>4.2k</b><span>GitHub stars</span></li><li class="outcome-chip"><b>500+</b><span>Active users</span></li></ul><section class="pwb-demos" aria-label="Demo"><h3 class="pwb-demos-heading">Demo</h3><figure class="pwb-demo pwb-demo-iframe"><div class="pwb-demo-aspect"><iframe src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/dQw4w9WgXcQ" title="Signal Forge in 90 seconds" loading="lazy" allow="autoplay; fullscreen; picture-in-picture" allowfullscreen="" referrerPolicy="strict-origin-when-cross-origin"></iframe></div><figcaption class="pwb-demo-caption">Signal Forge in 90 seconds</figcaption></figure></section><div class="pwb-narrative pwb-narrative-toggle" data-pwb-scope="proj-1"><input type="radio" name="pwb-view-proj-1" id="pwb-view-recruiter-proj-1" class="pwb-narrative-radio pwb-narrative-radio-recruiter" aria-label="Recruiter view" checked=""/><input type="radio" name="pwb-view-proj-1" id="pwb-view-engineer-proj-1" class="pwb-narrative-radio pwb-narrative-radio-engineer" aria-label="Engineer view"/><div class="pwb-narrative-toggle-row" role="group" aria-label="Narrative view selection"><span class="pwb-narrative-toggle-label">View as</span><label for="pwb-view-recruiter-proj-1" class="pwb-narrative-toggle-option pwb-narrative-toggle-option-recruiter">Recruiter</label><label for="pwb-view-engineer-proj-1" class="pwb-narrative-toggle-option pwb-narrative-toggle-option-engineer">Engineer</label></div><div class="pwb-narrative-pane pwb-narrative-pane-recruiter"><div class="prose"><p>Signal Forge assembles GitHub evidence into a defensible portfolio.</p><h3>Architecture</h3><p class="pwb-narrative-text"><span class="pwb-sentence pwb-sentence-verified" data-pwb-status="verified">Edge-deployed static generator with a Postgres source of truth.</span></p><h3>In a nutshell</h3><p>Shipped a dev-tool used by 500+ engineers, 4k+ stars.</p><h3>Technical detail</h3><p class="pwb-narrative-text"><span class="pwb-sentence pwb-sentence-flagged" data-pwb-status="flagged">The fact-extractor uses a two-pass LLM rubric with deterministic post-filters.</span></p></div></div><div class="pwb-narrative-pane pwb-narrative-pane-engineer"><div class="prose"><p>Phase 8.5 inlines the chatbot bootstrap so the publish target stays standalone.</p><h3>Architecture</h3><p>Static-site generator targeting Cloudflare Pages; per-portfolio Pages Function carries the chatbot retrieval corpus.</p><h3>In a nutshell</h3><p>Shipped a dev-tool used by 500+ engineers, 4k+ stars.</p><h3>Technical detail</h3><p>The fact-extractor uses a two-pass LLM rubric: extraction with structured-output JSON Schema, then deterministic post-filters to drop low-confidence facts and de-duplicate against existing rows.</p></div></div></div><section class="pwb-storyboard" aria-label="Guided tour"><h3 class="pwb-storyboard-heading">Guided tour</h3><ol class="pwb-storyboard-grid"><li class="pwb-storyboard-card"><header class="pwb-storyboard-card-head"><span class="pwb-storyboard-card-icon" aria-hidden="true">💡</span><span class="pwb-storyboard-card-num">01</span><h4 class="pwb-storyboard-card-title">What it does</h4></header><p class="pwb-storyboard-card-desc">Turns a GitHub history into a proof-backed portfolio site.</p><ul class="pwb-storyboard-claims" aria-label="Verified claims"><li class="pwb-storyboard-claim"><span class="pwb-storyboard-marker pwb-storyboard-marker-ok" aria-label="Verified" title="The verifier confirmed this claim against repo state">✓</span><span class="pwb-storyboard-claim-label">Reads N projects per portfolio</span></li></ul></li><li class="pwb-storyboard-card"><header class="pwb-storyboard-card-head"><span class="pwb-storyboard-card-icon" aria-hidden="true">🛠</span><span class="pwb-storyboard-card-num">02</span><h4 class="pwb-storyboard-card-title">How it works</h4></header><p class="pwb-storyboard-card-desc">9-step pipeline: fetch → extract → narrate → verify.</p><ul class="pwb-storyboard-claims" aria-label="Verified claims"><li class="pwb-storyboard-claim"><span class="pwb-storyboard-marker pwb-storyboard-marker-ok" aria-label="Verified" title="The verifier confirmed this claim against repo state">✓</span><span class="pwb-storyboard-claim-label">Uses Drizzle for Postgres</span></li></ul></li><li class="pwb-storyboard-card"><header class="pwb-storyboard-card-head"><span class="pwb-storyboard-card-icon" aria-hidden="true">📄</span><span class="pwb-storyboard-card-num">03</span><h4 class="pwb-storyboard-card-title">Worth a look</h4></header><p class="pwb-storyboard-card-desc">The pipeline orchestrator: state machine + retries.</p><div class="pwb-storyboard-snippet"><p class="pwb-storyboard-snippet-path"><code>src/lib/pipeline/orchestrator.ts</code></p><pre class="pwb-storyboard-snippet-code"><code>export class PipelineOrchestrator { /* ... */ }</code></pre></div></li><li class="pwb-storyboard-card"><header class="pwb-storyboard-card-head"><span class="pwb-storyboard-card-icon" aria-hidden="true">✓</span><span class="pwb-storyboard-card-num">04</span><h4 class="pwb-storyboard-card-title">Tested</h4></header><p class="pwb-storyboard-card-desc">Jest covers the helpers; integration tests cover the API.</p><ul class="pwb-storyboard-claims" aria-label="Verified claims"><li class="pwb-storyboard-claim"><span class="pwb-storyboard-marker pwb-storyboard-marker-ok" aria-label="Verified" title="The verifier confirmed this claim against repo state">✓</span><span class="pwb-storyboard-claim-label">1000+ unit tests</span></li></ul></li><li class="pwb-storyboard-card"><header class="pwb-storyboard-card-head"><span class="pwb-storyboard-card-icon" aria-hidden="true">🚀</span><span class="pwb-storyboard-card-num">05</span><h4 class="pwb-storyboard-card-title">Deploys</h4></header><p class="pwb-storyboard-card-desc">Cloudflare Pages auto-provisions per portfolio.</p></li><li class="pwb-storyboard-card"><header class="pwb-storyboard-card-head"><span class="pwb-storyboard-card-icon" aria-hidden="true">▶</span><span class="pwb-storyboard-card-num">06</span><h4 class="pwb-storyboard-card-title">Try it</h4></header><p class="pwb-storyboard-card-desc">Click through to the live site.</p><div class="pwb-storyboard-demo"><a href="https://signal-forge.example.test" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="pwb-storyboard-demo-link">Try it <span aria-hidden="true">↗</span></a><pre class="pwb-storyboard-clone"><code>git clone https://github.com/acme/signal-forge</code></pre></div></li></ol><figure class="pwb-storyboard-diagram"><figcaption class="pwb-storyboard-diagram-summary">Architecture</figcaption><pre class="mermaid pwb-storyboard-diagram-source">graph TD
  A[Repo] --&gt; B[Pipeline]
  B --&gt; C[Static Site]</pre><p class="pwb-storyboard-diagram-hint">Diagram source rendered with <a href="https://mermaid.js.org/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">mermaid.js</a>.</p></figure><script>(function(){try{if(typeof window==="undefined"||typeof document==="undefined")return;var nodes=document.querySelectorAll("pre.mermaid");if(!nodes||nodes.length===0)return;import("https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/mermaid@10/dist/mermaid.esm.min.mjs").then(function(m){var mermaid=m.default;mermaid.initialize({startOnLoad:false,securityLevel:"strict",theme:"default"});mermaid.run({nodes:nodes}).then(function(){nodes.forEach(function(n){var p=n.parentElement;if(p)p.setAttribute("data-pwb-mermaid-rendered","true");});}).catch(function(){});}).catch(function(){});}catch(e){}})();</script></section><div class="section-header" style="margin-top:48px"><h2 style="font-size:1.2rem">Built with</h2></div><ul class="tech-row"><li>TypeScript</li><li>Next.js</li><li>Drizzle</li></ul><section class="pwb-evidence-list" aria-label="Verified facts"><h3 class="pwb-evidence-heading">Verified facts</h3><ul class="pwb-evidence-items"><li class="pwb-evidence-item"><div class="pwb-evidence-claim"><div class="pwb-evidence-claim-line"><span class="pwb-evidence-tick" aria-label="Verified by the pipeline" title="This claim has been verified against the source">✓</span><span class="pwb-evidence-claim-text">Written in TypeScript</span><span class="pwb-evidence-source" title="Evidence type: dependency">from package.json</span></div><details class="pwb-evidence-details"><summary class="pwb-evidence-summary">Evidence</summary><div class="pwb-evidence-body"><blockquote class="pwb-evidence-quote">&quot;typescript&quot;: &quot;^5.4.0&quot; in package.json</blockquote><p class="pwb-evidence-ref"><span class="pwb-evidence-ref-label">Source:</span> <code>package.json</code></p></div></details></div></li><li class="pwb-evidence-item"><div class="pwb-evidence-claim"><div class="pwb-evidence-claim-line"><span class="pwb-evidence-tick" aria-label="Verified by the pipeline" title="This claim has been verified against the source">✓</span><span class="pwb-evidence-claim-text">Uses Drizzle ORM for the Postgres source of truth</span><span class="pwb-evidence-source" title="Evidence type: repo_file">from code</span></div><details class="pwb-evidence-details"><summary class="pwb-evidence-summary">Evidence</summary><div class="pwb-evidence-body"><blockquote class="pwb-evidence-quote">import { pgTable } from &#x27;drizzle-orm/pg-core&#x27;; 12 tables defined in schema.ts.</blockquote><p class="pwb-evidence-ref"><span class="pwb-evidence-ref-label">Source:</span> <code>src/lib/db/schema.ts</code></p></div></details></div></li><li class="pwb-evidence-item"><div class="pwb-evidence-claim"><div class="pwb-evidence-claim-line"><span class="pwb-evidence-claim-text">Server-side template rendering via renderToStaticMarkup</span><span class="pwb-evidence-source" title="Evidence type: readme">from README</span></div></div></li></ul></section><p style="margin-top:32px"><a class="btn-ghost" href="https://github.com/acme/signal-forge" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">View repository →</a></p></div></article></main><footer class="footer"><div class="container footer-inner"><span>© 2026 Jane Doe</span><span><a href="https://github.com/janedoe" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">GitHub</a> · <a href="https://linkedin.com/in/janedoe" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">LinkedIn</a></span></div></footer></body></html>"
`;

